heaviest_rainfall.status: Today's storm ranked 7th for total rainfall with 23.86mm having fallen, indicating an exceptionally wet day.  8.3mm per hour fell at points during the storm which lasted 31.0 hours.  The heaviest total rainfall occurred on 09 November 2025, dropping 47.89mm of rain over the 144.8 hour storm duration with a maximum rate of 24.6mm per hour.

heaviest_rainrate.status: A torrential downpour occurred on 02 September 2025 when the rain reached a maximum intensity of 34.3mm per hour.  This happened during a 15.0 hour storm when 21.19mm of rain fell.

longest_rain.status: Ranked 7th for lengthiest precipitation event, today's storm spanned 31.0 hours and was characterized by a peak rain intensity of 8.3mm per hour.  23.86mm of rain fell in total.  Rain fell for 144.8 hours on 09 November 2025 creating a new record that still lasts.  The storm produced a total of 47.89mm with a maximum intensity of 24.6mm per hour.
